				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Damage Shield<a name="61488"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 11 04 3:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I thought I'd share this for the other lowbies out there...
<br />

<br />
There is a guide to the maximum DS on the left there which got me thinking...  And experimenting...
<br />

<br />
In Old Seb recently I picked up a SS Bracer.  I've also got a Trouby Mace.  I twisted an Amped psalm (37 poison), and Rondo.  My DS was 43, just from my own equipment and songs at lvl 57, which surprised me no end because none of it is particularly Uber.  And further shows that the bard is capable of constant re-invention.
<br />

<br />
The good thing is that the SS Bracer is targettable, so this can benefit your whole group as well.  This is a good combo because there is some haste in there and some Atk, and room for another song.  Plus your own DPS is not hindered if you have a Trouby mace or a brass aug.
<br />

<br />
I'm gonna enjoy this next time my group is fighting something unslowable...</span></td>
