				<td colspan="2"><span>Don't forget shammy potions which you can carry yourself too, to add 34 points.  so SSbracer, songs, intruments, and amp, plus the potion... plus a few nifty items have DS components on them now.  should be easy for a well geared bard to push a 200 DS.  the shammy potions do not stack with the ranger ac/ds buff line though, so be careful if grouping with a ranger because you might waste doses, however their thorn shields will be better than the SSbracer buff (yet still stack with potion).  Lastly do not forget the nifty cleric reverse DS that they can cast on mobs... so with a druid/mage/ranger type in the group, and a cleric and a bard, I can imagine a 300point DS in effect.  But its nice to know that more than half of that comes from the bard =)</span></td>
